commit.message:
snap: Run tests

Added the missing `make check` to the overridden build stage to ensure
the snap build log contains the output of `procenv` as usual.

Added the additional test-specific build dependencies to the snap config file.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

scripts: Correct env path

The standard `env(1)` lives in `/usr/bin`, not `/bin`.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

scripts: Don't assume shell type

Make the machine details script more resilient to different
shell types and different installed compilers.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

scripts: Whitespace fixes

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

man: Add homepage

Add the canonical project homepage to the man page.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

usage: Show homepage URL

Also fixes a very long-standing buglet which was causing the output
of `--help` to be indented erroneously.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

configure: Fix nits

- Correct `AM_CONDITIONAL` test for `PACKAGE_URL`.

  Previously, this generated a non-fatal configure error message
  and since `PACKAGE_URL` wasn't being used was benign.

- Quote all parameters to `AC_INIT`.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

scripts: Improve machine details dump

Rework the machine details script to handle other systems.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

tests: Improve arg checker

Updated the argument checking script to support various JSON and XML
checkers (rather than just `xmlwf(1)` and `json_pp(1)`) and wrapped them
in new `check_json()` and `check_xml()` functions.

Also:

- Whitespace fixes.
- Remove last two redundant args to `_run_command()`.
- Added a `main()` function.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

CI: Disable homebrew for OSX

Homebrew is borked in Travis' OSX environment; updating `brew` triggers
openjdk to be built from source, which times out after 10 minutes of no
output.

Since we don't want Java and the Travis config never requested Java,
this is a pita. Therefore force homebrew to be disabled. The downsides of
this change are that on OSX:

- The `pr_list` unit tests are won't run (since the `libcheck` library
  won't be available).
- The XML and JSON tests in `src/tests/check_all_args` won't be run
  since `xmlwf(1)` and `json_pp(1)` (which is part of the `perl(1)`
  package) won't be available.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

copyright: Add more SPDX headers

Add copyright headers to files that didn't previously have one.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

get_user_info: check return value

Fixed "uninitialized value" bug detected by `cppcheck(1)`.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

docs: Fixed apparmor description

The description of `libapparmor` was actually the duplicated description

autoconf: Fix AppArmor and SELinux detection

The AppArmor and SELinux detection was broken (embarrassingly) due to
commit 6d31b517d0b425c908112d5f4d0f9582d86686bb which changed the
`AC_SEARCH_LIBS` `HAVE_THING=` values from `true`/`false` to
`yes`/`no`. That change broke the `AM_CONDITIONAL` calls which were
still looking for the old values, so the variables were never exported
correctly to `src/Makefile.am`.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

docs: Add snap details to README

Explain how to install the pre-built binary snap from the Snap Store.

Add a script to "sniff" for new symbols in both man pages and include

obvious.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

sysconf: Various fixes

- Removed duplicate entry for `_SC_EXPR_NEST_MAX`.

- Removed invalid `_SC_TYPED_MEMORY_OBJECT`

  The correct value is  `_SC_TYPED_MEMORY_OBJECTS`, which is already
  being displayed). The invalid value wouldn't have been displayed as the
  symbol won't have been defined.

- Added new entries for:
  - `_SC_2_PBS_CHECKPOINT`
  - `_SC_SS_REPL_MAX`
  - `_SC_STREAMS`
  - `_SC_TRACE_EVENT_NAME_MAX`
  - `_SC_TRACE_NAME_MAX`
  - `_SC_TRACE_SYS_MAX`
  - `_SC_TRACE_USER_EVENT_MAX`
  - `_SC_XOPEN_STREAMS`

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

sysconf: Fixed ordering

Ensured that all pathconf and sysconf values are displayed
alphabetically.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

prctl: Add missing entries

Added the following prctl values:

- `PR_GET_FP_MODE`
- `PR_GET_IO_FLUSHER`
- `PR_GET_SPECULATION_CTRL`
- `PR_GET_TAGGED_ADDR_CTRL`
- `PR_GET_THP_DISABLE`

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>

prctl: Fix PR_GET_UNALIGN

The prctl is `PR_GET_UNALIGN`, _not_ `PR_GET_UNALIGNED`! This would have
resulted in the value never being displayed since the (incorrect) symbol
won't have been defined.

Signed-off-by: James O. D. Hunt <jamesodhunt@gmail.com>
